# UIButtonVisualSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Drives the toggle button's image from its interaction state. Returns early until
SandboxConfigSingletonComponent is present; lazily creates UIButtonVisualStateSingletonComponent on
the first ready frame. Each frame it computes the button's state - pressed (a UIOnClickOneFrameComponent
for the toggle button) takes priority over hovered (a UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent), otherwise default -
and, only when that state changed since the previous frame, emits a UIUpdateImageUUIDOneFrameComponent
on the button with the matching texture.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Toggle button id and the three button texture ids; guard |
| UIOnClickOneFrameComponent | read | Pressed state for the toggle button |
| UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent | read | Hover state for the toggle button |
| BaseComponent | read | Locates the toggle button entity by UUID |
| UIButtonVisualStateSingletonComponent | write | Last-pushed image state (change detection) |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| UIButtonVisualStateSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; updated when the state changes |
| UIUpdateImageUUIDOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on the button only when its interaction state changes |
